CONTENT:

Download the brochure today to explore the curriculum and admission details.


Best wishes,

Mike Malefakis

President

Hello Alessandro,  I found your profile in this group that focuses on OPEN NETWORKING, so I presume you have an interest in this field. If I am mistaking, please excuse my intrusion and disregard my message, but if I am right, please keep reading, as I might strike your interest with what I am about to present.  My name is Radu, and I embarked on a journey as a LinkedIn Open Networker (LION) earlier this year. My aim was simple - to rapidly expand my network and leverage it to assist others in achieving their LinkedIn goals.  Today, I stand tall with 15,000+ connections. As promised to myself and to the LION community, it's now my turn to give back.  Here's my proposal for you, in five easy steps:  1. Connect with Me: By sending me a connection request, you'll instantly gain access to my expansive and ever-growing network. This can amplify your reach and visibility on this platform. I would send all the invitations from my side, but LinkedIn only allows me like 15 per day or so without triggering the algorithm. If by the time you read my message you can't see a connect button (make sure you click the MORE button to see it) it means I already reached the maximum connections allowed on LinkedIn, which is 30000. But even then, there is more that can be done.  2. Become a Featured Connection: Periodically, I'll be spotlighting a list of connections/followers in various LION groups, encouraging members to connect with those featured. This can be a boost for your profile and can help you garner more connections.  3. Be Active in My Community: Engage by liking, sharing, and especially commenting on posts. Active participation gets you noticed by other members more quickly. Your interactions can be the bridge to more meaningful professional relationships.  4. Embrace the LION Identity: Update your profile to specify that you're a LION/Open Networker. This lets others know you're open to connections and fosters a culture of openness. By doing so, you signal to the community that you're approachable and willing to connect.  5. Exclusive LION Group Invitations: If you've been eyeing certain LION groups but haven't been able to join, I can facilitate your entry based on my membership. Note that if you only FOLLOW me, I can't send you any group invites, we have to be CONNECTED.  In essence, this is an opportunity for mutual growth. The bigger our networks, the more opportunities we unlock for one another.  Also, if you check my profile, you will notice that I am involved in several educational projects, the LION thing is just a side project to grow faster, my main goal here isn't just to grow, but to create an organic community for my projects. I specialize in Sales, Marketing and Business Development, but I also have a background in Psychology, Journalism, Fitness and Nutrition. As a psychotherapist I also work with my mother on some medical educational projects so I convinced her to join my LION journey as well. It's funny, she entered the community 2 months after me but she's ahead of me already, standing at almost 20000 connections and growing fast.  Interested? Send me a CONNECTION REQUEST, and let's start this journey together. And if you wish, you can send my mother a connection request as well and I assure you she is going to accept it. Just to make sure, when you send the request, write "LION" in the connection note. Here is her profile as well: https://www.linkedin.com/in/gladiola-i-7a22a549/  Kind regards, Radu

CONTENT: Hello Everyone,  I am doing a little experiment which will benefit you and I in the end. I hate to ask this favor of you but it is important. I recently updated my skills that were getting a bit static from years past so I deleted the 99+ ones to add the new relevant ones for today. If you are ok with helping out, can you please endorse only my skills that are NOT 99+? You will have to scroll to the bottom of my profile to see them all and also expand to "See More". I would really appreciate this kind gesture. In return, I will do the same for you since you have helped out in this experiment. My goal is to reach 99+ on all the additions before the end of today.! Let's see how good our network really is.   *If you are not interested in helping out, go ahead and please delete this message and I apologize now for bothering you.  IMPORTANT: Please do NOT respond to this group message because no one likes to get caught up in the back and forth conversations. I will see if you endorsed those skills or if you did not. LI does have the feature to "Mute" the conversation so you do not get caught up in the back and forth but guess what, it doesn't work at all. It does nothing! I have logged a ticket for one of the many issues I have found.  Thanks in advance and kind Regards,  Christopher Brewster

Hello Allesandro,  Hope you are well ?  I'm excited to announce that in late November, the RAIN Group Center for Sales Research published our newest major benchmark research report on "The Top-Performing Sales Organization". Over the past three months, we've analyzed data in 8 sales performance categories from 472 research participants with sales forces from 10-5,000 sellers across industries and geographies.  Our goal was to answer a deceptively simple question: "What do Top-Performing Sales Organizations do (so) differently from everyone else? Which practices do they put in place that we can learn from to emulate their success ?"  I've just received the early results, and would like to set up a call with you as soon as possible to walk you through our main findings, and together discuss how to apply them in your context and environment.  In the call, we'll cover the striking differences between Top Performers, Middle Performers and Laggards, including:  ‚Ä¢	What the differences in win rates and other key metrics look like between Top-Performers and everyone else ‚Ä¢	How Top Performers are able to consistently motivate their salesforce for optimum and sustainable performance ‚Ä¢	How the maturity of their sales process, sales method, and strategic account management practices influence overall sales performance ‚Ä¢	How they achieve pricing in line with their value, avoiding the "double trap" of commoditisation and margin pressure ‚Ä¢	In which ways they create and communicate the full value they deliver to clients, thereby differentiating themselves and securing high-margin business ‚Ä¢	What the effect of being a ‚ÄúValue-Driving Sales Organization‚Äù is on metrics like revenue growth, pricing, win rates, and key employee turnover  This is a unique opportunity to develop a deeper understanding of what it takes to build a Top-Performing Sales Organisation. With 2016 around the corner, I can honestly think of no better time to spend 60 minutes on the phone together, and walk through these findings.  Which 1-2 timeslots could work for your personal 60-minute briefing call in the December?  Cheers,  Ljubisa

No worries.  That is a flaw in LinkedIn's message system.  Clicking to X out only removes you until someone makes another comment and then you are back in again.  Each time someone adds the the conversation, it pulls you back into it and you have to X out again.  It's a flaw they need to fix but nevertheless it works that way.   Honestly, I don't mind that much but I've seen other people before get very angry that they can't remove themselves and they and other keep posting to be removed.  The conversation itself I don't really mind being a part of, but it's all the "remove me please" messages and people getting angry that I don't like.    Todd
